      • getQualiferScopeFromFQName

        public static java.lang.String getQualiferScopeFromFQName(java.lang.String name)
        Returns the qualifier scope (i.e. qualifier + ".*" from the given fully qualified name or "*" if no qualifier exists. Example: getQualifierFromFQName("games.hockey.HockeyRoom1") returns "games.hockey.*"
        Parameters:
        name - - the fully qualified name
        Returns:
        the qualifier scope from the given fully qualified name

      • isValidQualifier

        public static boolean isValidQualifier(java.lang.String qualifier)
        Returns true if the given qualifier is syntactically valid. It does not guarantee that the qualifier will be appropriate for all methods. It does not guarantee any rooms with the qualifier exist on the server.
        Parameters:
        qualifier - - the qualifier
        Returns:
        true if the given qualifier is syntactically valid

      • isValidRoomID

        public static boolean isValidRoomID(java.lang.String roomID)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if the room ID is valid.
